<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Blue-Green Algae (Cyanobacteria)</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #2F4F4F;
            --primary-light: #3a5f5f;
            --secondary: #778899;
            --accent: #20B2AA;
            --light-bg: #f5f5f5;
            --dark-text: #2d3748;
            --border-color: #e0e0e0;
            --white: #ffffff;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: var(--light-bg);
            color: var(--dark-text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            background: var(--white);
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary);
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .info-section {
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #eaf2ff;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .info-section p:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .btn {
            display: block;
            margin: 25px auto;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        /* Back button */
        .back-button-container {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 5px;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        /* Highlight important terms */
        .highlight {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--primary);
        }

        .feature-list {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .feature-list li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        /* Responsive design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                margin: 15px;
                padding: 20px;
            }
            
            h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
            
            .back-button-container {
                position: relative;
                top: auto;
                left: auto;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
            }
            
            .back-button {
                position: relative;
                margin: 0 auto 20px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Back to Home Button -->
    <div class="back-button-container">
        <button class="back-button" onclick="goBackHome()">&#8592; Back to Parameters</button>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Blue-Green Algae (Cyanobacteria)</h1>
        <p>
            <span class="highlight">Blue-green algae (BGA)</span>, scientifically known as cyanobacteria, are photosynthetic microorganisms that can range in color from blues and greens to reds and blacks. Despite their name, they are not true algae but rather a type of bacteria capable of photosynthesis.
        </p>
        <p>
            While BGA can play a beneficial role in aquatic ecosystems by fixing nitrogen and carbon, they become problematic when overabundant, potentially depleting dissolved oxygen levels and producing harmful toxins.
        </p>

        <button class="btn" onclick="toggleInfo()">Show Detailed Information</button>
        
        <div class="info-section" id="moreInfo" style="display: none;">
            <h2>Ecological Impact</h2>
            <p>
                Monitoring BGA is critically important because they pose serious threats to:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Water quality and ecosystem stability</li>
                <li>Surface drinking water supplies</li>
                <li>Public health through toxin production</li>
                <li>Recreational water safety</li>
                <li>Aquatic life through oxygen depletion</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Detection and Measurement</h2>
            <p>
                Modern monitoring systems measure blue-green algae in real-time using <span class="highlight">in vivo fluorometry</span>. This advanced technique:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Directly detects the fluorescence of specific pigments in living algal cells</li>
                <li>Determines relative algal biomass with high accuracy</li>
                <li>Provides immediate results for rapid response</li>
                <li>Is not affected by interference from chlorophyll or turbidity</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Harmful Algal Blooms (HABs)</h2>
            <p>
                When conditions are favorable (warm water, abundant nutrients), BGA can multiply rapidly, forming harmful algal blooms:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Can produce potent toxins (microcystins, cylindrospermopsin, etc.)</li>
                <li>Create surface scums that block sunlight</li>
                <li>Deplete oxygen when they die and decompose</li>
                <li>Disrupt aquatic food webs</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Prevention and Management</h2>
            <p>
                Effective BGA management strategies include:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Nutrient control (reducing phosphorus and nitrogen inputs)</li>
                <li>Regular monitoring and early detection systems</li>
                <li>Public education about bloom conditions</li>
                <li>Water treatment adjustments during bloom events</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function goBackHome() {
            window.location.href = 'parameters';
        }

        function toggleInfo() {
            const info = document.getElementById("moreInfo");
            const button = document.querySelector(".btn");
            
            if (info.style.display === "none") {
                info.style.display = "block";
                button.textContent = "Hide Detailed Information";
            } else {
                info.style.display = "none";
                button.textContent = "Show Detailed Information";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>